The paper discusses the use of deep learning neural networks to learn the behavior of profitable traders in a financial market. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves the use of trading algorithms, which could be classified under the sub-category of trading (cs.TR). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of large volumes of data, which could be classified under the sub-category of data mining (cs.DM) or machine learning (cs.MA). Finally, the paper involves the study of market mechanisms, which could be classified under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
